address: Xã Vĩnh Trung, Huyện Vị Thuỷ, Tỉnh Hậu Giang
thought:
**Finding the New Administrative Unit for Xã Vĩnh Trung**

Okay, so I need to figure out what happened to "Xã Vĩnh Trung, Huyện Vị Thuỷ, Tỉnh Hậu Giang." First, a quick recap: old ward is Xã Vĩnh Trung, district is Huyện Vị Thuỷ, and the province is Tỉnh Hậu Giang.

Since provinces often get reorganized, I started with the big picture.  I remembered that Hậu Giang was merged.  A quick check of the relevant resolutions (60-NQ/TW) confirmed it: Hậu Giang became part of "Thành phố Cần Thơ."  So, any new ward information would have to be within the context of Cần Thơ.

Now, I had to dig through the specific resolutions to find any mentions of "Xã Vĩnh Trung" within Cần Thơ. I started with the most recent resolutions, looking for ward-level changes. I methodically went through each relevant resolution: 1654, 1662, 1667, and finally, 1668/NQ-UBTVQH15.

1654 (An Giang) was a no-go, wrong province. 1662 (Đồng Nai) was silent. 1667 (Khánh Hòa) also had a "Vĩnh Trung," but that was in Khánh Hòa, not Cần Thơ.

Finally, 1668 (Cần Thơ) showed promise. I carefully scanned each line. Line 45 mentioned "Vị Trung," but that wasn't "Vĩnh Trung." Line 46 had no relevant information. Then, there it was: Line 48. Bingo! It explicitly stated that "Xã Vĩnh Trung" was merged into a new ward called "Xã Vĩnh Tường."  The resolution number is 1668/NQ-UBTVQH15, line 48.

Therefore, "Xã Vĩnh Trung, Huyện Vị Thuỷ, Tỉnh Hậu Giang" is now part of "Xã Vĩnh Tường" in "Thành phố Cần Thơ."  Problem solved.

citation.header: 1668/NQ-UBTVQH15: Sắp xếp các đơn vị hành chính cấp xã của thành phố Cần Thơ
citation.line: 48. Sắp xếp toàn bộ diện tích tự nhiên, quy mô dân số của xã Vĩnh Trung và xã Vĩnh Tường thành xã mới có tên gọi là xã Vĩnh Tường.
